accessibility.text: Then, continuing with surprises, the camera follows the phone and shifts from the aeroplane setting, finding the flight attendant framed in a medium shot, surrounded by the rugged, breathtaking landscapes. The sounds of the plane are replaced by the vivid, ambient nature soundscape — rustling grass, distant bird calls, and a soft snorting of the horse. With a confident smile, she delivers the line: \"YOU DON'T HAVE TO REMAIN SEATED IN YOUR SEAT AT YOUR DESTINATION.\" As she speaks, the camera zooms out, revealing that she is in Patagonia, seated on a horse, holding bow and arrow in hand.
